     <font class="TallRed">Dear Tuuk<a name="109445078179095394">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          First of all, Tuuk, your post was... a bit long. <br /><br />Secondly, with regards to your comment about my beef with GW going to Yale and myself not being accepted to Virginia Tech:  I just don't like that nepotism was the deciding factor in his acceptance and not his own merits.  You'd think that someone who will eventually be president could get into college on his own or something... I don't know, it's disappointing.  Would I take advantage of the same situation if given the chance?  Yes I would.  But the issue I have here is this (and keep in mind, I really don't know too much about how Yale is funded; if it is completely funded by private means, they are excluded from this):  There is no logical reason why I should have to pay a proportionately equal amount of money to a state-funded university (such as Virginia Tech) when I have a less-than-equal chance of being admitted... which means that no one should be given that "leg up" birthright oppurtunity.<br /><br />Thirdly, I never said I was voting for Kerry, nor did I ever imply that I wouldn't vote for Bush simply because I'm jealous of his getting into Yale.  I believe that I said I would vote for Justice.  And by justice I mean not Kerry.  And also, not Bush.  That's right, Libertarian candidate Michael Badnarik is getting my vote, probably.  Zing!  Maybe he isn't the Personification of Justice, but I'm sure he's an alright guy.<br /><br />And as a sidenote, I am definitely not voting for Kerry because he supports the platform of affirmative action, AKA reverse discrimination.  I don't feel very strongly about many issues, but this one happens to be one of the ones that I do have an opinon on.  If anybody thinks that this platform is a good idea, please comment or post.  I'm interested to know if you guys really think it's a good idea or are just willing to bear it if it means that Bush is out of office.<br /><br />
          <div class="byline">
